"Constructing buildings to earthquake standards reduces seismic damage considerably. 51 \n\n# War Situations\nIt may seem obvious that the more intensive a combat is, the greater the number of people involved in it will be 52 and the greater the number of wounded. However, many other factors play a part as well: the degree to which combatants respect (or do not respect) the civilian population, 53 and the type of weapons used. Weapons now have greater blast effect and may cause delayed internal injury. The interplay of these factors prevents a quantitative approach."